Project Ado.TE

The Ado.TE Project is a practical system developed as part of the Python Full course. This system facilitates pet adoption, where users can register pets for adoption, request adoptions, and manage adoption requests.
Key Features

    Pet Registration: Users can enter detailed information about pets available for adoption, including name, photo, breed, description, location, and tags.

    Pet Filtering: Users can filter pets by city and breed to find those they wish to adopt.

    Adoption Requests: Users can request the adoption of pets available on the platform.

    Request Management: Administration of adoption requests, allowing approval or rejection of adoption applications.

Environment Setup

To run the project locally, follow the steps below:
Prerequisites

    Python 3.6 or higher
    Django 3.0 or higher
    MySQL database

Installation

    Clone the repository

    bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/adote.git
cd adote

Install dependencies

bash

pip install -r requirements.txt

Configuration

    Create an .env file in the project root with the necessary environment variables (see .env.example for reference).

    Configure environment variables for MySQL database connection in the settings.py file.

Apply migrations

bash

python manage.py migrate

Create a superuser

bash

python manage.py createsuperuser

Run the development server

bash

    python manage.py runserver

    Access the system

    Open your browser and visit http://localhost:8000.

Usage

    Log in as an administrator to manage pets, adoption requests, and users.

    As a regular user, register pets for adoption, filter pets by city and breed, and request adoptions.

Technologies Used

    Python
    Django
    HTML/CSS (Bootstrap)
    JavaScript (Chart.js)

Contributions

Contributions are welcome! Feel free to submit pull requests with improvements or bug fixes.
